						<summary>

						<p>Door-post of the entrance into the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-Chōḷadēva: Year 17 = 1199-1200 A.D. (?)</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged at the end. It records a gift of paddy made by the residents of Kaṇṇāḍipputtūr, for offerings to the deities Tiru-Anantīśvaramuḍaiyār, Sundarar and Nāyanār, and for three <hi rend="italic">sandhyā</hi> lamps.</p>						

						</summary>
